article.headline: Lehigh 28, VMI 26
article.story:
LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Eric Rath ran for three touchdowns
Saturday as Lehigh held off a surging VMI to win 28-26, spoiling
the Keydets' homecoming.

Rath carried the ball 19 times for 118 yards, with 1-yard
touchdown runs in the second and third quarters and a 2-yard
scoring run in the fourth quarter.

Julian Austin ran a fumble recovery 34 yards for a touchdown in
the first quarter. Mark Borda finished 20-for-29 for 223 yards and
three interceptions, including one that Robert Mason ran back 90
yards for the final touchdown of the game. Lehigh (2-1) fumbled the
ball seven times, losing it twice.

Two field goals and a 3-yard touchdown run from Nat Jackson had
VMI (1-3) close at 14-13 at halftime. The Keydets tried to fight
back in the fourth quarter with a 5-yard touchdown run from
quarterback Jonathan Wilson and the interception return.

Wilson finished 20-for-35 for 211 yards and two interceptions.
